@node not01 "ANYONE INTERESTED IN A PORT OF AXIA TO AMIGAOS?"

ANYONE INTERESTED IN A PORT OF @{B}AXIA@{UB} TO @{B}AMIGAOS@{UB}?
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

@{B}Wildcard  Design,  Inc.@{UB}  are  considering  porting  one of their games (@{B}Axia@{UB}) to
@{B}AmigaOS@{UB}   if   there   is   enough  interest  in  it  at  the  DOS  price.  (See
@{B}www.buydirect.com@{UB}  and  click  on  'Games'.  @{B}Axia@{UB}  is currently #5). If there is
enough  demand  for  it, they will look into porting. If ported, it would need a
minimum of the @{B}OCS@{UB} chipset.

@{B}Axia@{UB}  is  a  smooth top view, 360-degree scrolling space shoot-em-up game that's
unique  in  its egocentric control and display. (The world revolves around you!)
It boasts intense graphics & special effects, realistic gameplay, awesome music,
and spectacular sound effects.

Send  an  e-mail to @{I}John Delamore @{UI}at @{I}jdelamore@wcdesign.com @{UI}if you'd like to see
it  on  the @{B}AmigaOS@{UB}. Take a look at @{B}www.wcdesign.com/products/axia.html@{UB} for some
screenshots, or download the @{B}BeOS@{UB} or @{B}DOS@{UB} demo to take a look at how it plays.
