@{I}MILLENIUM GAMES @{UI}

To  celebrate  the  Millenium,  @{B}Alive  MediaSoft@{UB} are holding the world's biggest
@{B}Amiga@{UB}  software  survey in years. We have always prided ourselves in our ability
to  track down old games for people through our "Classic Search Service" as well
as stocking a large range of classic titles in our catalogue.

Over the last 10 years, the @{B}Amiga@{UB} has given us thousands of brilliant games (not
to  mention  just  as  many crap ones!). It can sometimes be difficult for us to
choose which games people will want.

To  celebrate  all  the great games, we launching the "MILLENIUM SURVEY" to find
out the greatest @{B}Amiga@{UB} games of all time.

By  voting,  you can help your favourite games to see the light of day again. On
June  1st,  @{B}Alive  MediaSoft@{UB} will announce the survey winners giving you the top
ten  from  each catagory like Best Adventure, Best Beat 'em Up and so on. During
the  months running up to the announcements, @{B}Alive MediaSoft@{UB} will put in 110% to
obtain  the  winning  games.  All  winning titles will go on sale from June 1st.
Obviously, many of the games will be limited availability. So if say, 100 people
vote  for  @{B}Sim  City 2000@{UB}, and we can only get 50 copies, we will give those who
voted  the  first  opportunity to buy a copy before onening sales to the general
public.

Vote now, and receive your chance to reserve your favourite all time game!

As  if  all  that isn't enough, @{B}Alive@{UB} are celebrating this "Millenium Survey" by
giving  away hundreds of pounds worth of prizes. All voters will be entered into
the prize draw for a chance to win one of the prizes below:

  * 1st prize: £100 Alive gift certificate
  * 3 x 2nd place prizes of £20 Alive gift certificates
  * 10 x 3rd place prizes of free software titles.

On  @{B}Alive@{UB}'s  web  page,  you will soon be able to download a list of @{B}Amiga@{UB} games
from  brand  new  titles,  dating  right back to the good old days of @{B}Elvira@{UB} and
@{B}Project X@{UB}! This little slice of nostalgia may help jog your memory and give some
ideas for your vote.

Full details of how to enter along with a voting form are going out to all @{B}Pulse@{UB}
subscribers.  If  you  don't  already  subscribe  to @{B}The Pulse@{UB}, you can do so by
emailing  us your postal address. Subscription is totally free. It is simply our
catalogue  and  supplementary  magazine  with compliments from @{B}Alive@{UB}. To request
your    copy    of    @{B}The   Pulse@{UB},   send   your   full   postal   address   to:
@{I}jenniealive@innotts.co.uk @{UI}

================================================================================

@{I}@{B}THE PROPHET @{UB}@{UI}

A  quick  note  about a game @{B}Alive@{UB} will be releasing around late April/early May
this  year:  @{B}The  Prophet@{UB}.  This  is  a dungeon master style adventure game made
exclusively  for the @{B}Amiga@{UB} by an up and coming team based in Leicester, England,
headed by a talented chap called @{I}Mark Ford. @{UI}

Full  details  and  demo  will  follow  in  time,  but to give you an idea, it's
hard-drive only for floppy users, or CDrom installable on hard-drive.

This  is  going  to  be  a  huge  adventure  game,  with astounding features and
incredible playability. Full details to come soon....

================================================================================

