@node not05 "DELSYD SOFTWARE WANT TO HEAR FROM YOU"

@{B}DELSYD SOFTWARE@{UB} WANT TO HEAR FROM YOU
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

@{B}Delsyd Software@{UB}, the first development team to announce a game for the @{B}Amiga NG@{UB},
are  taking a survey to see how fast the average @{B}PPC@{UB}-based @{B}Amiga@{UB} is, so they can
keep this in mind during the programming phase of @{B}The Last Patriot@{UB}.

This  survey is due to the fact that the @{B}Amiga NG@{UB} dev. boxes are nonexistant, so
they don't see a reason why they should postpone the release of @{B}TLP@{UB} for the @{B}PPC@{UB}.
Their  new target release date for @{B}TLP@{UB} is November-December 1999. This will be a
limited  release,  that  is,  they will publish the game themselves in a limited
quantity,  and  sales  from  this  limited  release will help them upgrade their
manufacturing  facilities,  so  they can release more copies of @{B}TLP@{UB}. An @{B}Amiga NG@{UB}
release  is  still  planned,  but recent delays with the dev boxes could push it
back a bit.

And,  if  this  wasn't  good  enough  news,  @{B}Delsys  Software@{UB} have more games in
development. Below is a list of future releases with planned release dates.

        @{B}The Last Patriot@{UB}                 Nov/Dec 1999
        @{B}The Adventures of DP Dog in 3D@{UB}   2nd Half 2000
        @{B}DP Tennis@{UB}                        1st Quarter 2000
        @{B}DP Kart@{UB}                          Nov/Dec 1999
        @{B}I-40:Cross Country Rally@{UB}         2nd Half 2001
        @{B}Destitution@{UB}                      2nd Quarter 2000

All titles will be @{B}PPC@{UB}/@{B}Amiga NG@{UB} compatible.

If  you have any questions, email @{B}Delsyd Software@{UB} at @{I}delsydsoftware@yahoo.com @{UI}or
visit their WEB site @{B}www.geocities.com/siliconvalley/foothills/2705@{UB}
