@node not18 "CLICKBOOM INTRODUCES THE CLICKBOOM AMIGA 'PORTAL'"

@{B}CLICKBOOM@{UB} INTRODUCES THE @{B}CLICKBOOM AMIGA@{UB} 'PORTAL'
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE @{UI}

Toronto,  February  11,  1999:  @{B}clickBOOM@{UB} proudly introduces The @{B}clickBOOM Amiga@{UB}
"Portal"

The  "Portal"  is a new way for @{B}clickBOOM@{UB} users to access online information, be
it  their record at @{B}clickBOOM@{UB}, or @{B}Amiga@{UB}-related content -- it's a dynamic online
database allowing for much closer interaction with the Web.

@{I}"@{B}clickBOOM @{UB} and  @{B}clickboom.com @{UB} are  undisputedly  at the top of the @{B}Amiga @{UB}games
market.", @{UI} says  @{I}Sofia  Tsiotsikas, @{UI}PR at @{B}clickBOOM@{UB}. @{I}"It is our intention to use
this  leverage  and extensive web-creation knowledge to provide @{B}Amiga @{UB}users with
the next-generation web experience -- The "Portal". Our target is now beyond the
games scope, and we are confident The "Portal" will provide all @{B}Amiga @{UB}users, not
just  players,  a great service. We strive to push technology forward, hence The
"Portal" -- the first and only on @{B}Amiga." @{UB}@{UI}

Although  this is @{B}clickBOOM@{UB}'s first step into a non-gaming area, The "Portal" is
created  with  the  same  high-quality  standard  you'd  expect  to receive from
@{B}clickBOOM@{UB}.

The "Portal" consists of the following sections:
  * AUCTIONS
  * NEWS CENTER
  * COMMUNICATION CENTER
  * STATUS INFORMATION
  * PREFERENCES

@{I}AUCTIONS @{UI}

The "Portal"'s main attraction is the fully automatic real-time online "Auction"
section. This is where all the action is -- you can bid on or sell @{B}Amiga@{UB}-related
items  at  the one and only place of its kind on @{B}Amiga@{UB}. Finally there is a place
for  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  users  to be able to trade their hardware in a simple and absolutely
private manner.

The "Portal" is the place where you will find the best @{B}Amiga@{UB} deals, guaranteed.

If  you  have  an @{B}Amiga@{UB}-related item to sell, The "Portal" is the place, hold an
auction and have other @{B}Amiga@{UB} users bid on it. It's fully automatic, create a new
auction  in  less than 5 minutes, and don't worry about it until you make a sale
at the highest offered price.

Full details on how "Auctions" function, are available at The "Portal".

@{I}NEWS CENTER @{UI}

"News  Center"  takes  a  whole  new  step  at addressing @{B}Amiga@{UB} news flow on the
Internet.  We  guarantee  you  that  "The  News  Center"  is  the simplest, most
comprehensive, one of a kind, customizable @{B}Amiga@{UB} news section on the Internet!

Instead  of  creating  another news-reporting site @{B}clickBOOM@{UB} worked with leading
@{B}Amiga@{UB}  news  sites  behind  the  scenes to create a single place on the Net from
which you will start your news search.

The  idea  behind  the  "News  Center" is very simple - every time one of the 50
@{B}Amiga@{UB} news sites currently supported gets updated, their news will appear at the
News Center!

The  news  section  is  unbiased,  because  the  actual site owners update their
section  at  The "Portal"! Moreover, you can customize which news sites you want
to have top priority.

Never  again  will  you  have  to  spend time searching sites, only to find they
haven't been updated. Just come to The "Portal" and you will immediately see the
latest  headlines  of  ALL  the sites, then with just one click go to the actual
site  and  read  the  news. Moreover, the "Portal" will remember which sites you
prefer and have them waiting at the top of the section at your next visit!

We  would  also like to take this opportunity to invite all @{B}Amiga@{UB} news sites not
currently featured at The "Portal", to contact us.

@{I}COMMUNICATION CENTER @{UI}

The "Communication Center" allows registered @{B}clickBOOM@{UB} users to communicate with
@{B}clickBOOM@{UB}  in  a  more  direct  approach and receive more efficient responses to
their  questions.  Through  a  simple  web interface you can leave a message for
@{B}clickBOOM@{UB} and your message will get the highest priority, because it will not go
to  the same pool of email letters that non-registered users got to. Then simply
check back at any time for a response.

@{I}STATUS INFORMATION @{UI}

@{B}clickBOOM@{UB}  registered users can also access their status information online. The
"Portal" recognizes when you are visiting, so it prepares dynamic content that's
tailored  for  you  only.  This  makes the "Portal" better and friendlier than a
regular  web  site. Get information such as how many BOOM$ you have; which games
you have registered; what is the status of your last order, etc.

@{I}PREFERENCES @{UI}

The  "Preferences"  section allows one to easily update his personal information
such  as change of email or mailing address. It also allows for customization of
the "Portal", such as which News sites you prefer to always see at the front.

The "Portal" is located at @{B}clickboom.com/portal@{UB}

The  "Portal"  is  not finished, nor will it ever be, it's a constantly evolving
flux, just like the Web itself. So, be prepared for even more content very soon,
as we get the engine running.

Best Regards,
@{B}clickBOOM@{UB}
