@node not23 "THE WORLD FOUNDRY NEWS UPDATE"

@{B}THE WORLD FOUNDRY@{UB} NEWS UPDATE
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

From: @{I}E Collins @{UI}@{I}collins-e@dnet.co.uk @{UI}

@{I}@{B}The World Foundry @{UB}website moves to a new home @{UI}

Very soon the @{B}TWF@{UB} website will move to it's new home (@{B}www.worldfoundry.com@{UB}) with
a  new look to it. This should make it much easier to remember where our site is
as  the Monolith redirection has stopped working and the old site's true address
is quite a mouthful.

@{I}@{B}Explorer 2260 @{UB}Development update @{UI}

Development  of  @{B}E2260@{UB} has been developing well with much of the station systems
which  is  the  heart of the game making good progress. Work is also progressing
well  on  several  of the game editors that will be used to create data used for
the game (and will most likely be included with the final release).

Screenshots  won't  be  appearing for at least a few months I'm afraid. We would
like  a  release  of  a demo in the 2nd quarter and the finished game in the 3rd
quarter  but  none  of  this can be guaranteed so both demo and finished product
releases could well fall back into the 3rd and 4th quarters respectively.

@{I}@{B}Maim & Mangle @{UB}is revived @{UI}

After the game being originally cancelled after @{I}George Hornmoen's @{UI}departure from
the  team  to  pursue a @{B}PC@{UB} games development career, the rights and code for the
game  were  passed  onto us. With work needed heavily on @{B}E2260@{UB}, trying to find a
new  team to revive @{B}M&M@{UB} was put on the back burner. We now have found a new team
to work on the game and development has restarted on the game.

Some  of  the  features  have  been updated because as there are more @{B}PPC Amiga@{UB}s
available  and  better  3D  support we feel it would help make a better game and
stand   out   against  similar  realtime  wargames  such  as  @{B}Napalm@{UB},  @{B}Operation
Counterstrike@{UB},  @{B}Forgotten  Forever@{UB}, etc. Test have been performed on a 3D engine
and  we  have decided it is viable and so has been given the go ahead. Only test
graphics  of  the  3D  engine have been used so when we have progressed a little
with the engine

So  here is the info for those who have not heard of the game before and updated
feature list planned for the game.

================================================================================

Game Information

@{B}Maim  &  Mangle@{UB}  is a @{B}Dune 2@{UB} or @{B}Command & Conquer@{UB} style realtime wargame for the
@{B}Amiga@{UB}  computer  but will have plenty of unique features never seen before on an
@{B}Amiga@{UB}.  It will be one of the most technically demanding @{B}Amiga@{UB} games released to
date.  However,  despite  all of the wizardry involved, game-play will always be
the top priority.

Feature List

Some of the features you can expect to see in @{B}Maim & Mangle@{UB} are:

  * Total 3D:
        Thats  right!  When @{B}Maim & Mangle@{UB} was originally started to be developed
        it  was  to  have a 3D landscape but things have changed since then with
        improved  @{B}Amiga@{UB} systems supporting 3D hardware acceleration so this time
        the  game  will  be in total 3D. The landscape, buildings, vehicles will
        all  be in 3D. The player will be able to move around the map and rotate
        and zoom in on units to check for damage and info on them.

        Since  the  landscape  is  in  3D,  gameplay can be different from other
        similar  games of this type as units can hide behind hills, infantry can
        scale  cliff faces and canyons, vehicles can fall off cliffs, etc. Units
        will  progress  slower  up  a  slope and faster down a slope. Units on a
        hilltop  will  have  a  longer  range of fire, however, they will have a
        'blind' spot immediately below them.

  * Multiplayer games via TCP/IP:
        @{B}Maim  &  Mangle@{UB}  will  have full TCP/IP support, so whether you have two
        @{B}Amiga@{UB}'s  linked  together over a serial cable, or they are on a network,
        you will be able to fight your friends to the death!

  * Save option for multiplayer games:
        Hey,  waging a full out assault takes time, and you might not be able to
        fit  it  into  one  session.  So  we've included the provision to save a
        multiplayer game.

  * Night-time combat: (1)
        Present  day  wars don't always take place during the day-light, and the
        wars  of  the  future will be no different. Therefore, night-time combat
        will also be present in @{B}Maim & Mangle@{UB}. To complement this, infantry will
        have  flashlights,  vehicles  will  have  headlights  &  bases will have
        searchlights.  Additionally, night-time vision equipment and flares will
        also play an integral part on the @{B}Maim & Mangle@{UB} battlefield.

  * Weather effects:
        As  all  battles  do not take place during the day, likewise they do not
        always  take  place  during  fair weather. Thus, weather effects such as
        rain  storms, dust storms, fog, etc. will also be encountered within the
        game.

  * Way-point navigation:
        To  complement the movement currently found in games of this style, @{B}Maim
        &  Mangle@{UB}  will  have  a 'way-point' style of directing your units. This
        will  allow  the  player  to tell the units to avoid known landmarks and
        enemy encampments.

  * Light Sourcing: (1)
        Explosions  and  lights  in  @{B}Maim  &  Mangle@{UB}  will  also  light  up  the
        surrounding  terrain. This will be especially stunning in the night-time
        battles. Plus many more!

In  addition  to  the  above  features, @{B}Maim & Mangle@{UB} will include several other
features such as a R & D element [akin to Genesia], an on-line library system of
known units, and an extensive plot to support the action!

(1)  Visual  effects of this nature may require a 3D Hardware accelerated or @{B}PPC
Amiga@{UB} to make the most of it.

Predicted System Requirements
  * @{B}Amiga@{UB} computer. Minimum @{B}040@{UB} processor.
  * @{B}PPC@{UB} boards supported from @{B}Phase 5@{UB} or @{B}G3@{UB} card from @{B}Escena@{UB}.
  * @{B}WarpOS  PPC@{UB}  kernal  will  be used. We will provide installation scripts for
    installing  @{B}WarpOS@{UB}  and  a  detailed  FAQ  for  those  people who experience
    problems using @{B}WarpOS@{UB} programs.
  * Minimum 8MB Ram.
  * CD drive (recommended 4x).
  * Hard Drive (uncertain at this time how much space will be needed).
  * GFX  Card Recommended (essential for those with only an @{B}ECS Amiga@{UB}). @{B}AGA@{UB} will
    also be supported.
  * @{B}Warp3D  V2@{UB}  driver system will be used to provide an independent of hardware
    standard for 3D on the @{B}Amiga@{UB}.
  * Modem (33.6+ recommended) and internet account for network games.
  * @{B}AHI@{UB} installed.

Support for @{B}68k Amiga@{UB}s has been decided for now but may have to be reassessed as
the  3D  engine  becomes more advanced. Possibilty of a restriction to a @{B}060@{UB} and
GFX card if speed is not good enough in lower systems.
